TSX-V-listed Galane Gold has decided to terminate the contract of CFO Gavin Vandervegt. He has served as Galane’s CFO since October 2016 and will remain with the company for a three-month transitional period. Galane chairperson Ravi Sood explains that the Galane board of directors is undertaking a review of its senior management team with a view to closer aligning it with the company’s growth plans over the next two years and the shift in the company’s focus with the addition of the Summit gold mine, in New Mexico. The company also holds gold assets in South Africa and Botswana.